<HEADLINE> UN Council Mourns Passing Away of Mitterrand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council
on Monday expressed mourning for the death of former French
President Francois Mitterrand.
</P>
<P>
The former president aged 79 died on Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
"It is with great sadness that we have received this morning
the news of the passing away of former President, Francois
Mitterrand," Council President John Weston of Britain read in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
President Mitterrand has played a pivotal role in the history
of his country, said the statement, and his political life spans
five decades, during which he played an active and influential
role, as a Cabinet Minister, as a political leader and as a
statesman.
</P>
<P>
After the statement was read, council members were invited by
John Weston to rise and observe a minute of silence in tribute to
the memory of President Mitterrand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
