<HEADLINE> Moi Mourns Over Mitterrand's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- President Daniel arap Moi today
praised late French President Francois Mitterrand as a leader
whose vision was "a valuable legacy to the whole world."
</P>
<P>
"The whole world will miss President Mitterrand's charm,
warmth and courage which he jovially displayed even when he knew
his health was failing," Moi was quoted by the official Kenya
News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mitterrand died of cancer early this morning at the age of 79.
</P>
<P>
Moi recalled Mitterrand's contribution to a closer tie between
Kenya and France, saying he had approved numerous French aid
projects to Kenya worth million of dollars during his 14 years in
power.
</P>
<P>
"The loss of President Mitterrand has robbed France and the
rest of the world," said the Kenyan President. 
</P>
</TEXT>
