<HEADLINE> Zaire Plane Crashes, Killing 250 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A cargo plane crashed into a
crowded market in the centre of the zairean capital Kinshasa
today, killing at least 250 people, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
An official of the International Committee of the Red Cross
was quoted as saying that most of the victims were women and
children who had been packing the city centre market of
corrugated iron and wooden shacks.
</P>
<P>
"Many of the bodies were multilated. The plane ploughed
through the market for about 100 metres before it came to a halt.
It is still belching flames and clouds of black smoke," the
report said.
</P>
<P>
A fire crew from the nearby Ndolo airport from where the
Antonov aircraft took off rushed to the scene and tried to dampen
the flames.
</P>
<P>
Wreckage from the aircraft was scattered across the site.
</P>
<P>
"The aircraft tried to take off but it only got a few metres
off the ground, then it disappeared and there was an explosion,"
said Gothie Mukoka, who was at the airfield when the plane took
off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
