<HEADLINE> Mitterrand's Death Big Loss To S. Africans: Mandela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- President Nelson Mandela
today considered the death of former French President Francois
Mitterrand as "a great loss to the people and government of South
Africa."
</P>
<P>
Mitterrand died of cancer at 8:30 gmt this morning. He was 79
years old.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released by the presidential office, Mandela
said he had learnt "with great shock" of the passing away of
Mitterrand.
</P>
<P>
"Mitterrand was more than a colleague and brother to me. He
was a staunch supporter of the struggle for democracy in South
Africa," said Mandela in the statement.
</P>
<P>
"And after last year's democratic elections in South Africa,
he was among the prominent world leaders who put the success of
our democracy and economic development high on the agenda of
their countries' programs," said Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Mandela had sent a message of condolences to
President Jacques Chirac through the South African Embassy in
Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
