<HEADLINE> Pakistan, UK to Cooperate in Rooting out Drug Menace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Britain have
reaffirmed their cooperation in rooting out drug menace.
</P>
<P>
The statement was made here today when Prime Minister Benazir
Bhutto met visiting British Home Secretary Michael Howard.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Benazir told the British official that her
government is determined to combat the drug business.
</P>
<P>
While meeting Howard, Pakistani Interior Minister Nasirullah
Khan Babar also briefed the British guest about the measures
adopted by Pakistan to eliminate the drug abuse and trafficking in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Howard arrived here Saturday for a three-day official visit to
Pakistan to discuss the drug issue, illegal immigration and other
issues of mutual concern.  
