<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Greece to Enhance Agricultural Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot and Greek Agriculture
Ministers met here today to review the course of the
implementation of a Greco-Cypriot cooperation program in the
agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
According to an official press release, the two sides
expressed full satisfaction with the work done so far and the
activities taken place, especially those concerning the exchange
of experience and data in all the fields of the broad agricultural
sector.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed on the activities of the two ministries
during the first half of 1996, under a cooperation program in
agriculture signed in May 1994.
</P>
<P>
The activities concern the exchange of data, training/education
and exchange of experts in all the fields of the broad
agricultural sector such as agriculture, water resources,
veterinary services and fishery.
</P>
<P>
They also decided to work out the details of the new two-year
cooperation program to be signed later this year in Athens.
</P>
<P>
Expressing satisfaction with the course of implementing the
cooperation program, Cypriot minister Costas Petrides underlined
the significance of the cooperation program between the two
countries in the field of agriculture, especially Greece's
experience for the preparation of Cyprus in its course toward the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
Greek minister Theodoros Stathis stressed that his current
visit here was a display of determination for further
strengthening of the cooperation program between Greece and Cyprus
in the agricultural sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
