<HEADLINE> 11 Killed in Road Accidents in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and
51 others injured in two separate road accidents in Pakistan
today, according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Four people, including a bride, were killed while 29 others
injured when a bus carrying a marriage party collided with a
tractor trolley in the south of Punjab province today.
</P>
<P>
The injured, six of whom in serious condition, were immediately
rushed to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Another seven people were killed and 22 injured in a head-on
collision between a bus and a wagon in Punjab today.  
</P>
