<HEADLINE> Importance of Shelterbelts Emphasized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Getting China's largest
shelterbelt to cover vast areas of northeast, north, and northwest
China is vital to the country's ecology and to the economic
development of central and western China to help people there
eliminate poverty.
</P>
<P>
This point was emphasized by Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun at a
conference on the completion of the second-phase of the
shelterbelt project, which was opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the completion of the second-phase of work on
the shelterbelt, which started in 1986, was because of the great
effort made by many people.
</P>
<P>
During the past 17 years of construction work, a total of 18
million ha of desolate area has been covered with green plants,
with the forest cover rate in the three areas rising from five
percent in 1977 to the current nine percent, according to data
provided at the conference.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, 87 work units were given citations and 168
workers were praised for their great contributions to the
shelterbelt construction work.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
