<HEADLINE> Japan's Current Account Surplus Continues Falling in  November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Japan's current account surplus
continued falling in November on the back of continued import
growth, dropping 26.5 percent from a year earlier, the Finance
Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The surplus in the current account, measuring goods, services
and transfer payments such as grant aid, totaled 7.02 billion
U.S. dollars, falling for the third consecutive month, the
ministry said in a preliminary report.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose a marginal 1.4 percent while imports advanced a
large 13.9 percent, the ministry said.  
</P>
