<HEADLINE> Pudong New Area Gets Over 10 Million US Dollars Daily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area, in China's
largest metropolis, set a record in 1995 by establishing on
average 2.3 Sino-foreign joint ventures and absorbing 10.9 million
U.S. dollars' worth of overseas investment daily.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, overseas investment has kept on
growing there since the area opened to the outside world in 1990.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Pudong took in a total of four billion U.S. dollars
and set up 838 foreign-funded enterprises, bringing the total
number to 3,501 enterprises and 14 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
More large projects with investments of more than 10 billion
U.S. dollars have been established here, with the number now 265
and total overseas investment, 6.61 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The investment structure has also been optimized, with tertiary
industry projects now numbering 1,900, with overseas investment of
6.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises in the area are also producing
better economic results. About a third of the 280 joint ventures
in new and high-tech industry have been put into operation,
creating a output value of 11 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Breakthroughs have also been made in utilization of overseas
investment, including issuing stock by Sino-foreign co-operative
enterprises and joint ventures in the BOT form. 
</P>
</TEXT>
