<HEADLINE> The First General-Use Credit Card in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The first credit card for use
with every bank was issued today in south China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Experts agree that the Intergrated Circuit -- or IC -- card is
of great importance to China's financial sector.
</P>
<P>
The card was jointly issued by the Hainan branches of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, the Agricultural Bank of
China, the People's Construction Bank of China, and the Bank of
Communications for use in a network.
</P>
<P>
Card-holders can deposit or withdraw money at designated places
in the province, or use it in designated shops or hotels.
</P>
<P>
Different from ordinary credit cards, the IC card can hold more
information and is more difficult to be forged or used by the
wrong people.
</P>
<P>
The card uses a cipher code, so that it requires no other
identification when it is used.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
