<HEADLINE> China's Largest Offshore Gas Field in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Ya13-1, China's largest offshore
gas field, which began to supply natural gas to Hong Kong on
January 1, will offer gas to Hainan Province from tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Located 91 kilometers south of Hainan, China's largest special
economic zone, the gas field is scheduled to provide Hong Kong
with 2.9 billion cubic meters, and Hainan with 500 million cubic
meters through a network of undersea pipes.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will mainly use the gas to generate power, and Hainan
to produce chemical fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the construction said that the
platform and production facilities are designed to last 30 years,
and the undersea pipes, 40 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
