<HEADLINE> Greek Exports GO Up 72% Over Last Seven Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Greek exports have increased 72
percent in the past seven years, amounting in value to eight
billion ECU, the Greece's Exporters Federation said in its latest
report today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, issued by the Federation of Exporters
of Northern Greece (SEBE), Greek exports totalled 4.6 billion ECU
in 1988 while in 1994 the figure was 7.9 billion ECU.
</P>
<P>
Most Greek exports are destined for European Union countries,
followed by countries in north Africa and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In 1994 Greek exports to EU countries amounted to 4.3 billion
ECU, while expports to countries in north Africa and the Middle
East to 1.08 billion ECU.
</P>
<P>
Another interesting factor is that exports to Balkan countries
increased sixfold between 1988 and 1994 and from 112 million ECU
jumped to 632 million ECU.
</P>
<P>
Greek products having the greatest demand are, according to the
report, unprocessed foodstuffs, minerals-asphalt and processed
foodstuffs and beverages. nditem


08/01/96 16:00 GMT
nnnn
</P>
