<HEADLINE> Soeharto Calls for Better Indonesian Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
today called for efforts to enhance the competitiveness of the
country's products in order to secure a due place for itself in
world trade nowadays.
</P>
<P>
He made the call when presenting the "Upakarti Presidential
Award" to outstanding businessmen who have successfully promoted
the partnership scheme with entrepreneurs of small-scale
industries.
</P>
<P>
"The country's industrial sector has to produce quality
products with higher competitiveness," he said, adding that
resources in Indonesia should be made better use of.
</P>
<P>
In anticipation of the free trade era, the president stressed
that necessary preparations have to be made now.
</P>
<P>
According to Soeharto, small-scale industries in Indonesia
employ some two million people at the end of the fifth Five-Year
Development Plan, which accounted for about one percent of the
country's population.
</P>
<P>
Such a development is encouraging, but not enough, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He called on all related agencies and major businessmen to
extend assistance in the development of small-scale industries.
</P>
</TEXT>
