<HEADLINE> State Council Adopts Two Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The 41st Executive Meeting of
the State Council presided over by Premier Li Peng today discussed
and adopted two regulations in principle.
</P>
<P>
The regulations concerned use of apparatus and weapons by
Chinese police and foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Regulation on the Use of Apparatus and Weapons by the
Police of the People's Republic was an amended version of the
Rules on the Use of Weapons and Apparatus by the People's Police
of 1980.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations provide clear guidelines on when police can
use weapons in order to ensure better security and protection of
the Chinese people, and an effective check on illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
The Regulation on Foreign Exchange of the People's Republic of
China is intended to help the current foreign exchange system
better adjust to a market economy. The previous regulation was
made in December 1980. Experts agree that China's foreign exchange
system has seen tremendous changes during the past several
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
