<HEADLINE> UK to Strengthen Anti-Drug Cooperation with Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The United Kingdom and
Pakistan will strengthen their cooperation to fight against drug
production and trafficking, a visiting senior British official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference at the British High Commission
in Islamabad, Michael Howard, the British Secretary of State for
the Home Department, said that drug issue was one of the major
topics during his current visit.
</P>
<P>
Howard said that most of the drugs produced in Afghanistan were
transported to other parts of the world through Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
"Britain is one destiny of those drugs," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
So it is an international problem which needs to be solved
through international cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that during his visit, he held talks with Pakistani
Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto, Interior Minister Nasirullah Babar,
and top officers of the Pakistani Anti-Narcotics Forces on
anti-drug cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan has a long border with Afghanistan, so it is not easy
to take effective actions to curb the drug trafficking," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But we hope that more will be done through the anti-drug
cooperation between the UK and Pakistan," he added.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not say anything about how to strengthen the
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Howard started his three-day visit to Pakistan from Saturday,
which concentrated on drug-related issues and immigration matters.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, Howard was so tight-lipped that he did
not answer a single question about the immigration directly.
</P>
</TEXT>
