<HEADLINE> Europe to Hold First Social Policy Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Europe's first forum on social
policy will be held in Brussels between March 28 and 30.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by Padraig Flynn, European
Commissioner responsible for Employment and Social Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner said he was fulfilling an undertaking made in
the White Paper on European Social Policy, launched in July 1994.
</P>
<P>
"The first European Social Policy Forum will allow the
Commission to bring together as many representative voices as
possible, to hear an exchange of views and to debate the key
issues of the day," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Flynn, the Comite des Sages (Committee of Wise
Men), chaired by Portugal's former Prime Minister Maria de Lourdes
Pintasilgo, will prepare a report on fundamental social rights and
their future fulfillment within the European Union.
</P>
<P>
"Participants will also focus on four topics: employment, equal
opportunities, social security, and the future of working life,"
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
