<HEADLINE> Arzu Wins Guatemalan Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Alvaro Arzu has won the
Guatemalan presidential election by promising to fight corruption
and crime and to steer the country on the path to prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Arzu, the candidate of the pro-business National Advancement
Party, won the election with 52 percent of the second-round
vote. He overturned the early lead of his populist rival Alfonso
Portillo as votes poured in from his Guatemala City base.
</P>
<P>
He had been mayor of Guatemala City and the country's foreign
minister before entering the presidential race. He is expected to
be sworn into office on January 14.
</P>
<P>
This central American country, with a population of 8.32
million, returned to democracy in 1985 and Arzu is the third
president since then. 
