<HEADLINE> Canada Stresses Support of Lebanon's Sovereignty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of the Canadian House of
Representatives Gilbert Parent stressed here today that his
country supports Lebanon's sovereignty and independence within its
internationally recognized borders.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized Canada's support of the implementation of
U.N. Security Resolution 425, which calls for an Israeli
withdrawal from all the Lebanese territories.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after holding talks with Lebanese House
Speaker Nabih Berri in the Parliamentary Building, Parent pointed
out that the problem of Palestinians in Lebanon can be resolved
through negotiations between parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian house speaker arrived in Beirut Sunday on a visit
to Lebanon, during which he will hold talks with Lebanese
political and religious leaders.
</P>
<P>
Calling on Lebanon to attend the multilateral talks which will
be sponsored by Canada and in which the problem of Palestinian
refugees in Lebanon will be discussed, Parent underlined that
Lebanon should not be afraid of that talks.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his country's readiness to make a serious
contribution for seeking a solution to this problem.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that there are about 500,000 Palestinian
refugees living in Lebanon, most of whom are residing in dozens of
refugee camps scattered all over the country.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian house speaker said that he conveyed to Lebanese
officials his country's concern about what is happening in Lebanon
and in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
He expressed a "big" optimism on the prospect of achieving a
peace agreement in the region, especially in the light of the
resumption of the Syrian-Israeli peace talks just before the end
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Parent also expressed his belief that progress in the
Syrian-Israeli peace talks will lead to progress on the Lebanese
track of peace talks, in view of the "firm relations" between
Lebanon and Syria.
</P>
<P>
He noted that if a peace does not prevail in the Middle East
region, there will be no peace in any part of the world.
</P>
<P>
Parent held a meeting earlier today with Lebanese Maronite
Patriarch Nasrallah Boutros Sfeir, the spiritual leader of
Lebanon's Maronite Catholic community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
