<HEADLINE> 20 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkish narcotics police seized
20 kilograms of heroin in Istanbul and detained five suspected
drugs smugglers, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
here today.
</P>
<P>
Anatolia said that the Turkish police confiscated the heroin
during the operation against drug trafficking in Yesilyurt
district in Istanbul, which was produced in Van Province in
eastern Turkey and brought via southeastern Diyarbakir.
</P>
<P>
The seized heroin is worth about 17.72 million U.S. dollars in
international market, said Anatolia.
</P>
<P>
Tuncay Yilmaz, chief of the anti-smuggling department of the
Turkish police, said that in 1995 the Turkish police seized 2,397
kilograms of heroin, 73 kilograms of base morphine, 56 kilograms
of cocaine, 112 kilograms of opium, 9,731 kilogams of hashish and
51, 139 kilograms of anhydride acid. In its serious fight against
the drug smuggling activities, Yilmaz said, the Turkish police
arrested 4,359 people last year.
</P>
<P>
About 1,800 police officers are now taking part in combating
the illegal drug trafficking. 
</P>
