<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Remains One of World's Safest Cities--Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Despite a slight increase in
overall crime cases last year, Hong Kong remained one of the
safest cities in the world, a senior Hong Kong police official
said today.
</P>
<P>
Hui Ki-on, the commissioner of the police, told a press
conference that the number of overall crime cases rose by 4.6
percent to 91,886 last year, but the rise was mainly attributable
to increases in woundings, various thefts and detected narcotics
cases.
</P>
<P>
He said that the crime detection rate in Hong Kong remained
steady at 52 percent which is very high by international
standards.
</P>
<P>
Hui said it was most encouraging to see a decrease in violent
crime cases, especially robberies involving genuine firearms and
pistol-like objects, which dropped significantly by 35.7 percent
and 11.6 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
He added that the local police force will make greater efforts
to fight against various crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
