<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-08 11:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Rural Conference Outlines Major Tasks for 1996-2000 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Stabilize and improve the Party's rural policies, deepen
agricultural reform and speed up the pace of opening up of
agricultural sector;
</P>
<P>
-- Transform agricultural growth model, and developing
high-yield, high-quality, low-consumption and high-efficiency
agriculture;
</P>
<P>
-- Input more into the aid-the-poor projects. The central
government has decided to increase one billion yuan of discounted
loans for poverty-relieving annually in the next five years; and
</P>
<P>
-- Work for the sustainable development of agriculture by
sternly controlling on population increase, protecting arable land
and ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The conference acknowledged that it is an arduous task to
fulfil the target set for the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to the grand plan set for the year 2000, the country
will register total grain output of some 490 billion to 500
billion kg, ensure farmers to lead a fairly comfortable life and
help 70 million poor farmers overcome poverty.
</P>
<P>
The conference also noted that there are some favorable factors
for the country's agricultural development in the coming few years.
</P>
<P>
The food consumption demand for the 1.2 billion population, the
rapid growth of the industrial and service sectors all form a
strong driving force for agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
The historic experience show that the production of
agricultural products always has its ebbs and tides, the
conference said. The country's current grain production is just in
a period of fluctuations and is carrying with itself seeds of new
and further development.
</P>
<P>
China has a great potential for the development of agricultural
resources and scientific utilization in the sector, the conference
said.
</P>
<P>
The reform in grains purchase and sale mechanism and the rising
in grain and cotton prices have aroused the farmers' enthusiasm
for the growing of food grains.
</P>
<P>
The conference called for the relevant departments to utilize
current favorable conditions to fulfil the target set in the ninth
Five-Year-Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
The major tasks in the agricultural sector this year is to
accelerate paces of construction of arable land and water
conservancy projects and to stabilize cereals growing acreage at
110 million ha and cotton planting acreage at six million ha.
</P>
<P>
Also, a batch of advanced and practical agricultural techniques
will be further spread and the pace of forestry construction
speeded up.
</P>
<P>
Among others, problems such as relatively low grain prices,
methods concerning supply and marketing of chemical fertilizers
and heavy burdens on farmers, are expected to be listed higher on
this year's agricultural agenda and coped with conscientiously.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
