<HEADLINE> APEC Meeting on Human Resources Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 8 (Xinhua) --The 18 members of Asia Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) began their two-day senior officials
meeting on human resources here today, to be followed by the
ministerial meeting.
</P>
<P>
The week-long meetings will focus on sustainable development of
human resources in the region, the development of small and medium
industries, welfare of overseas contract workers and transfer of
technology to less developed countries.
</P>
<P>
The senior officials are from the labor, education, trade and
industry ministries or cabinets of the APEC-members economies.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will set the stage of the first-ever APEC
ministerial meeting on economic resource development which will
take place on January 10 and 11.  
</P>
