<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Myanmar Ties Can Be Rated as Example: CPPCC Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, said here today that Sino-Myanmar ties can be rated as
a good example of good-neighborly relations.
</P>
<P>
Li described as "of historic significance" the ongoing visit to
China by Senior General Than Shwe, chairman of the State Law and
Order Restoration Council of the Union of Myanmar, and predicted
that the visit will open up a new chapter in Sino-Myanmar
relations.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Than Shwe at the Great Hall of the
People at noon today, Li said that China and Myanmar are close
neighbors joined by rivers, mountains and roads, and share
long-standing friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Myanmar relations have been "very good" and the two
countries have respected, understood, supported and learned
from each other all these years, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Now both countries face the common task of accelerating
economic development and improving their peoples' living
standards, the CPPCC chairman said.
</P>
<P>
"Myanmar boasts rich resources, a correct policy, strong and
effective leadership and hard-working people, and has broad
prospects for development," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Noting the strong complementarity between the two economies and
their co-operation potential, Li expressed the hope that bilateral
exchanges and co-operation would be raised to a new height.
</P>
<P>
Than Shwe echoed Li's view on bilateral economic
collaboration. He voiced the hope that his visit would bring new
results to the deepening of bilateral economic co-operation.
</P>
<P>
The friendship and co-operation between the two countries is of
great significance to the stability and development of this
region, Than Shwe added.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the CPPCC chairman hosted a banquet in honor
of the Myanmar visitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
