<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-08 09:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Confers with Myanmarese Leader (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Than Shwe said that Myanmar was encouraged by the great
economic achievements China has made in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the satisfactory development of bilateral ties to
the profound friendship between senior leaders of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He told Jiang that the main purpose of his visit is to
strengthen the bilateral ties, as well as to learn from China's
experience in developing its economy.
</P>
<P>
Than Shwe noted that his country would like to further expand
the relations of mutual benefit and co-operation between the two
countries, adding that the stable political situation and
developing economy of Myanmar have helped to pave the way for the
expansion of the two-way trade.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence
and the 10 Principles set forth at the Bandung Conference, Myanmar
will positively involve in the stability, peace and development in
the region and strive to promote its ties of friendship with its
neighbors in Southeast Asia and in the world at large, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China is very glad to see the achievements Myanmar
has made over recent years in stabilizing its political situation,
realizing national reconciliation, developing its economy,
upholding its traditional culture and expanding ties with other
countries.
</P>
<P>
China would like to increase its friendly co-operation with
Myanmar in various fields, Jiang said. China will continue to
encourage its enterprises to conduct mutually beneficial
co-operation with Myanmar so as to promote the two-way trade to a
new stage.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Myanmar's positive and independent
foreign policy. He noted that China would like to enhance
discussions with Myanmar on international and regional affairs in
order to safeguard the peace and stability in the region and the
interests and rights of the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Jiang and Than Shwe participated in a signing
ceremony for three Sino-Myanmarese co-operative documents -- a
bilateral co-operation agreement on economy and technology, an
agreement on the Chinese government's supply of loans to the
Myanmar government, and an agreement on bilateral cultural
co-operation.  
</P>
