<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Confers With Myanmarese leader (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that the Sino-Myanmar good-neighborly and friendly ties have
great vitality and bright prospects.
</P>
<P>
He made this remark during his talks with visiting Senior
General Than Shwe, chairman of the State Law and Order Restoration
Council of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Than Shwe arrived here Sunday for a one-week official goodwill
visit to China at the invitation of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
During today's talks Jiang expressed his convinction that the
current visit by Than Shwe would push the bilateral friendly ties
to a still higher level.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is both a good neighbor of China and one of the
countries which had established diplomatic relations with China at
an early stage, Jiang said, adding that the Five Principles of
Peaceful Co-Existence initiated by the two countries in the 1950s
have made great contributions to safeguarding peace and stability
in the world, as well as setting a good example for peaceful and
friendly coexistence among neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he noted, although the international situation
has changed dramatically, bilateral ties have enjoyed smooth and
stable development, exchanges of high-level visits have been
maintained, and fruitful exchanges and co-operation have been
conducted in the fields of politics, economy and trade, as well as
culture.
</P>
<P>
The 46 years after the forging of diplomatic ties between the
two countries have proved that the bilateral friendly ties, on the
basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence, have great
vitality and prospects, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that furthering such ties complies with the interests
of the two countries and will be beneficial to peace and stability
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for Myanmar's adherence to the
one-China policy.
</P>
</TEXT>
