<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Up By Half US Cent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Australian currency closed
stronger against the greenback today, rallying by more than half a
US cent.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar, which was traded between 74.58 and 74.82
US cents, ended at 74.70 US cents, up from 74.13 US cents last
weekend.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers expected the local dollar to remain near those
levels tomorrow and to test the 75 US cent line later this week.
</P>
