<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Ends Highest In 23 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A strong rally in the gold
sector gave a big fillip to the Australian stock market, which
registered a 23-month high close today.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries Index, the key market indicator, ended at
2,274.9 points, gaining 14.2 points from the previous close of
2,260.7 points.
</P>
<P>
This was the highest closing point in 23 months since February
1994, when the leading market indicator reached 2,305.4 points.
</P>
<P>
The local bourse was boosted by a strong surge in gold index,
which ended 62.5 points stronger at 2,046.7 points, up by three
percent.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials Index gained 9.7 points to close at 3,386
points from 3,376.3 points last Friday.
</P>
<P>
While the All Resources Index had a big jump of 18.4 points to
1,437.1 points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 257.7 million shares, with a value
worth 540.43 million Australian dollars (402.62 million US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
