<HEADLINE> Nanjing Marks 20th Anniversary of Zhou Enlai's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 people from all walks
of life in this capital of east China's Jiangsu Province gathered
today to mark the 20th anniversary of the death of Premier Zhou
Enlai (March 5, 1898--January 8, 1976).
</P>
<P>
The gathering was held at the Meiyuan New Village, where from
May 1946 to March 1947 the late premier led a delegation of the
Chinese Communist Party to negotiate with the Kuomintang
government until the Kuomintang authorities launched an all-out
civil war. The residence of the Communist Party's delegation was
turned into the Meiyuan New Village Memorial Hall after the
founding of New China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
During the gathering Zhou Erhui, a relative of the late
premier, and students from the "Zhou Enlai Class" of the Meiyuan
Middle School and the "Deng Yingchao Class" of the No. 9 Middle
School placed baskets of flowers before a bronze statue of Zhou
Enlai.
</P>
<P>
Deng Yingchao, who died in 1992, was Zhou Enlai's wife.
</P>
<P>
Those present also read several poems to commemorate their
beloved late leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
