<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Lions District 411, an
international charity organization, has committed 1.5 million
U.S. dollars for programs in Uganda aimed at fighting blindness
and other eye related diseases in the country.
</P>
<P>
