The organization is also intensifying similar programs in
other countries including Kenya, Ethiopia and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
According to Dodhia, there are 50 million blind people in the
world, 80 percent of whom can be treated, according to Dodhia.
</P>
</TEXT>
