<HEADLINE> CAS Environment Research Brings Huge Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS), China's top research institute, has completed a four-year
research program on comprehensive environmental control, making 180
million yuan (about 21.7 million US dollars) in economic benefits.
</P>
<P>
According to today's overseas edition of the "People's Daily",
this is the first time China has conducted such a research program
since its founding in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the program was intended to rationally develop
and use natural resources and improve the deteriorated ecological
system in a comprehensive way.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 researchers from the CAS' 50 institutes have
undertaken 11 pilot projects involving three main fields: how to
improve the fragile ecological system, how to rehabilitate mining
areas and how to develop diverse biological techniques for
protecting the environment.
</P>
<P>
Thirty items of technology developed by the researchers have
been applied to environmental control on 44,000 ha of land, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
The program, which has passed state assessment, will serve as a
basis for improving China's forest and marine ecological systems,
as well as for protecting rare and endangered animals and plants,
the paper said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
