<HEADLINE> High-Yield Rice Passes State Assessment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A new technique which can
raise the per-ha yield of ratooning rice by 150 percent to 3,750
kg, has passed a state technical assessment here.
</P>
<P>
The technique was developed by scientists at the Chongqing Farm
Products Research Institute and has proved successful after
experiments carried out on 1,000 ha of paddy fields for four years.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing cultivates ratooning rice on 166,600 ha, accounting
for 30 percent of China's total acreage of such rice. However, the
per-ha yield has traditionally been around 1,500 kg.
</P>
<P>
The new technique also makes the rice more resistant to
diseases and insect pests, said Ren Tianju, head of the research
group which developed the technique. 
</P>
