<HEADLINE> Mechanization Boosts Anhui Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Oxen are gradually being replaced
by a wide variety of farm machinery in Anhui, a leading grain
producing province in east China.
</P>
<P>
The combined power of farm machinery in Anhui has reached 18.05
million kw, a provincial agriculture official said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995 the area cultivated by machinery had
expanded to 2.82 million ha, making up 65 percent of the total
farmland in the province. The ratio was 30 percent higher than
that of 1990. Some 80 percent of rural transport is now done by
motor vehicles.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1995 period, during China's Eighth Five-Year
Plan, the province popularized the use of mechanical sowers and
harvesters and engaged in comprehensive utilization of grain
stalks.
</P>
<P>
Individual farmers were the major buyers of farm
machinery. Local statistics show that farmers bought 5.4 billion
yuan-worth of farm machinery in the same period, 3.1 billion yuan
more than the figure for the 1986-1990 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
