<HEADLINE> Shanghai Expanding Green Coverage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- This, China's most populous
city is concentrating on planting more lawns, trees and flowers to
improve the local ecology and beautify its environment.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, the urban area has 667.2 ha
of public green land at present averaging 1.4 sq m per capita and
double the 1980 figure.
</P>
