<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Bans Import Of Chemicals Affecting  Ozone Layer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will ban imports of
all types of chemicals which affect the ozone layer in the upper
atmosphere, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Research indicates that the ozone layer is already 20 percent
depleted by various chemicals reaching the upper atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The thinning of the Ozone layer, experts say, results in many
forms of ill-effects to both plant and animal life. It also can
cause skin cancer in humans.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Sri Lanka imports about 300 tons of CFCs, which are
primarily used in air conditioners and refrigerators, from France,
Belgium and India annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
