<HEADLINE> India to Announce Dates for General Elections Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- India's Election Commission is
expected to announce specific dates for the Lok Sabha (lower
house) elections within the next few days, the Hindustan Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The three-member commission will hold a meeting with Indian
government officials on January 10 for preliminary discussions on
arrangements for the coming general elections.
</P>
<P>
The commission, which began to function from January 7 or
exactly six months before the new lower house of parliament is
formed, will choose the general election date and dates for the
elections to six assemblies (State parliament).
</P>
<P>
The commission will also make decisions about the elections to
the Rajya Sabha (upper house) where 70 vacancies are to be filled
by April.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister P.V. Narasimha Rao announced on Saturday that
the general elections will definitely be held in April, but the
exact date remains undecided.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, during consultations between the commission and
political parties, all parties except the ruling Congress Party
favored general elections by late February or early March. The
Congress wanted them in April.
</P>
<P>
Chief election commissioner T. N. Seshan is said to be in favor
of elections in February or March, while the other two on the
commission are reportedly in favor of holding a dialogue with the
government on the dates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
