<HEADLINE> Agri-Food Industry Becomes Biggest EU Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Europe's agricultural food
industry has topped the European Union's table of industrial
sectors, with annual turnover of 590 billion U.S. dollars, local
press reported.
</P>
<P>
Some 17,000 enterprises employing 2.3 million people across the
EU are involved in the agri-food industry, accounting for 16
percent of EU industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
Livestock products make up the lion's share of output of the
agri-food industry with an annual production of 200 billion
dollars, followed by alcoholic drinks with 95 billion dollars and
grain products with 56 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France were the biggest producers, accounting for
20.4 percent and 20.1 percent of turnover respectively, while
Belgium was the smallest, contributing 3.2 percent to the
industry. 
</P>
