<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Private Bus Operators on Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's private bus
operators went on a three-day strike today, crippling transport in
the country, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The bus operators, who were not permitted by the government to
increase bus fares, have made alternate demands seeking relief in
other ways.
</P>
<P>
They have demanded three pairs of duty free tires annually, the
reduction of import duty on spare parts by 35 percent, and the
import of reconditioned vehicles at cheaper prices.
</P>
<P>
