of diesel and engine lubricants, cutting the insurance premiums to
100 US dollars from 400 US dollars and a reduction in the route
permit fee.
</P>
<P>
The All Ceylon Private Bus Societies Federation says that the
strike has initially been scheduled for three days but it will
last until their demands were met.  
