The threat followed recent moves by state agencies to allow the
hiring of unskilled workers from neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The decision to allow imports of foreign labor was
"unacceptable" and would have an adverse effect on local workers,
according to Prathuang Saengsang, vice president of the Thai Trade
Union Congress.
