<HEADLINE> Implementation of New Project in Myanmar Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Tin Oo urged local
administrative personnel at a meeting here on Sunday to endeavor
for the implementation of the new five-year project.
</P>
<P>
The new five-year project (1996-2001) will begin in April this
year and end in March 2001.
</P>
<P>
According to The New Light of Myanmar today, Tin Oo, the
second secretary of the Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration
Council, said the four-year project (1992-96) to be ended in March
this year will realize an average increase of 7.5 percent in gross
domestic product.
</P>
<P>
He noted that good economic ground work has been laid and the
state has been on the path to long-term development.
</P>
<P>
The state has formed an industrial development committee to
boost production and to stabilize commodity prices while plans are
being implemented extensively to help fulfill requirements of the
people, Tin Oo said.
</P>
<P>
He called on private manufacturers to boost their production
for all-round development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
