<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-08 03:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wages Massive Anti-Porn Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China's massive winter
anti-pornography campaign has turned out to be fruitful and a lot
of illegal CD and VCD products and their suspects have been seized
since it started two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the national anti-pornography office
urged the governments at all levels to make more efforts and score
greater achievements in the campaign against pornography and
illegal production and selling of pirated products.
</P>
<P>
So far, a number of cases and units concerning production and
selling of illegal and pornographic materials have been looked
into.
</P>
<P>
In Shenzhen, a fast-growing coastal city that neighbors Hong
Kong, a total of 460,000 pirated audio and video products were
seized in a recent police raid. The manufacturers and salesmen of
these porno materials have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
A book titled "Odd Sexual and Marital Customs" has been
declared pornographic and its publisher has been arrested. The
book violated the Party's policies on nationalities and religions,
and relevant departments have been urged to confiscate it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
