<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hoyer-Larsen Wins Title in Austrian Badminton Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Denmark's Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen,
Europen men's champion in 1992 and 1994, defeated Li Kwang Jin of
South Korea 3-2 in the final to win the title in an Austrian
badminton invitational tournament in Dornbirn on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hoyer-Larsen came from behind to outplay the South korean 5-15,
15-4, 15-13.
</P>
<P>
He entered the final after beating Jens Olsson of Sweden 18-16,
15-7 in a semi-final match while Li Kwang Jin edged Jeroen Van
Dijk of the Netherlands 5-15, 15-4, 15-13 in another semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The tournament organizers awarded to the champion an automobile
and a gold-plating badminton racket. 
</P>
</TEXT>
