<HEADLINE> Zhuhai to Open New Air Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- An additional 20 domestic air
routes will be opened by this special economic zone in south
China's Guangdong Province this year, according to Yu Rongai,
general manager of the Zhuhai Airport Corporation said.
</P>
<P>
This will bring the number of domestic air routes in Zhuhai to
40, double the 1995 figure, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Zhuhai Airport will be capable of handling 1.5
million passengers and the number of weekly flights will increas
to 200 this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Yu, the airport handled 270,000 passengers as well
as 3,000 tons of cargo and mail last year with its weekly 90
flights.
</P>
<P>
Since the airport went into operation last year it has opened
40 booking offices in Zhuhai and neighboring areas, providing
convenient service for passengers, Yu said.
</P>
<P>
To date, some 17 airline companies are operating flights to and
from Zhuhai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
