<HEADLINE> Giant Lizard Discovered in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A 1.12-meter-long lizard
weighing two kg has been captured in Suining County in central
China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the overseas edition of the "People's Daily", last
month a local farmer discovered the lizard hibernating in the
mountains.
</P>
<P>
The next day the farmer took the lizard to the local wildlife
protection department and was given an award for his efforts for
wildlife protection.
</P>
<P>
Lizards, which mainly live in south and southwest China, are
under the state's top protection along with the giant panda and
golden monkey.  
</P>
</TEXT>
