<HEADLINE> 113 People Die in Snowstorms in Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 113 people were
killed and up to 5 million U.S. dollars of damage were caused by
snowstorms which swept central and northern areas of Kazakhstan at
the end of December, the Kazakh central television reported this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The government has sent 46 million kopeks (710,000) in relief
aid to the disaster area. The snowstorms, which began on December
23, damaged electricity and communication lines and power
stations and causing losses of 200-350 million kopeks (3.2-5.4
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
