<HEADLINE> Ningbo Educating Parents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,400 schools
instructing parents how to train their children have been
established in almost all parts of the city of Ningbo in east
China's Zhejiang Province, enrolling 350,000 parents since the
first one was set up in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The Qiu Aizhen Township parents school takes in parents each
September, when the primary school students start school.
</P>
<P>
Parents spend their spare time taking courses and examinations
on how to use more scientific ways to communicate with their
children, and certificates of graduation are issued according to
their achievements.
</P>
<P>
Mao Yiyi, a worker in a local factory, changed his way of
educating his daughter after attending a parents school. Her
daughter became a good student and he became an excellent cadre in
his factory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
