<DOCNO> XIE19960108.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-08 02:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo Port Handles More Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- This major port in east China's
Zhejiang Province handled 68.5 million tons of goods last year,
ten million tons more than in the previous year, ranking fourth
among all of China's ports.
</P>
<P>
During the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1991-1995) seven berths were
added to the port, increasing its handling capacity by 19.95
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Over this period the port's cargo handling grew by 21 percent a
year. Last year workers at the port unloaded 261,000 tons of goods
from a 300,000-dwt ship in 91 hours, at a rate reaching that of
the world's advanced ports.
</P>
<P>
Now Ningbo has established trade relations with more than 400
ports in 79 countries and regions. It handled 160,000 standard
container units last year, up 27.8 percent over 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
