<HEADLINE> Two Percent Growth Predicted for German Economy in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- German Economics Minister Guenter
Roxrodt today predicted 2 percent growth in the economy in 1996,
but warned unemployment could hit four million over the winter.
</P>
<P>
In a radio interview, Roxrodt said there would be no economic
boom this year, only sustained growth at a low speed.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless is likely to hit 4 million in winter but
a drop is expected in spring. The unemployment situation will
improve this year in the eastern part of Germany, but it is
difficult to predict for the western part, he said.
</P>
<P>
Roxrodt said the government will present an economic growth and
job creation program at the end of January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
