<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists to Explore Earth's "Three Poles" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists will explore
the South Pole, the North Pole and Qomolangma (Mount Everest) over
the next eight years.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today by the non-governmental China
Scientific Exploration Association.
</P>
<P>
"The expedition to the 'three poles' will be a milestone in
history," said Jin Lei, one of the expedition's organizers.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are abundant natural resources in the three
regions, and the scientists will research subjects having close
connection with the national economy.
</P>
<P>
These subjects will include the greenhouse effect, the origin
of life, ecological balance, and biological diversity, Jin said.
</P>
<P>
The team members will be chosen from the fields of natural and
liberal sciences, and journalists will be included. However, the
total composition of the expedition has not yet been decided.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
