<HEADLINE> Russian Diplomat Charged of Spying in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Swiss federal authorities
confirmed today that a Russian diplomat in Geneva had been
declared as a persona non grata recently because of spying
activities, Swiss television reported.
</P>
<P>
The news was first disclosed by Swiss German-language newspaper
Sonntagsblick a few days ago and was confirmed Sunday by Swiss
Federal Department of Justice and Police.
</P>
<P>
The Russian diplomat, whose name had not been disclosed, had
been working in the Russian mission to the UN office at Geneva for
about one year before being charged of conducting illegal
intelligence activities.
</P>
<P>
He was already called back on December 21 after being declared
as a persona non grata by the Swiss government, Swiss media
reported.
</P>
<P>
However, the Swiss authorities has not given any details on
what kind of intelligence the Russian diplomat collected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
