<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Accuses Syria of Depriving Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkey today accused Syria of
depriving Turkey's share of the Asi River's (Orontes) water.
</P>
<P>
"It is our intention to raise the question of the Asi River
whenever the water question arises," Foreign Ministry spokesman
Omer Akbel said.
</P>
<P>
"The question of the Asi will inevitably be brought up by the
Turkish side in any water forum," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Asi River originates from Lebanon, passes through Syria
and flows into the Mediterranean sea within the Turkish province
of Hatay.
</P>
<P>
Syria has built two dams on the river, with two reservoirs
planned. Turkey says the planned reservoirs will further decrease
Turkey's share of its water.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's move is seen as an effort to counter Syria's protest
against it over the construction of another dam on the river.
</P>
<P>
Syria has lobbied some Arab and western countries to accuse
Ankara of polluting the river by building the dam. Seven Arab
countries issued a declaration in Damascus last month, calling
upon Turkey to sign a "just agreement" with Syria on water sharing.
</P>
<P>
The Asi River issue has attracted the attention of Arab and
western diplomats in Ankara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960108.0221 </DOCNO>
