<HEADLINE> ANC Involvement In Kwazulu/Natal Killings denied </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Deputy President Thabo
Mbeki today denied the recent killings in the Kwazulu/Natal
province were caused by party conflicts between the African
National Congress (ANC) and Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP).
</P>
