the IFP against the ANC as some media reports described.
</P>
<P>
The police have been carrying on an investigation into the
Christmas Day massacre at Shobashobane near Port Shepstone in
Kwazulu/Natal, which caused 19 deaths and huge property damages.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki said the investigation would find out who was behind the
violence caused by 600 armed gangsters who swept across the area,
setting fire on stores, houses and government buildings.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local media insisted on the partisan aspect of the
ethnic clash. Reports said an estimated 14,000 lives have been
claimed by ANC-IFP conflicts in Kwazulu/Natal during the last few
years. 
