<HEADLINE> Canadian PM Mourns Death of Mitterrand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 8 (xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien today expressed his condolences on the death of former
French President Francois Mitterrand.
</P>
<P>
Chretien told reporters at the airport before his departure for
India on a trade mission that Mitterrand was a good friend of
Canada and the world lost a "great political leader".
</P>
<P>
Chretien said Mitterrand had a lot of influence in Europe,
particularly in the difficult situation in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to offer my condolences to his family, and to the
President of France (Jacques Chirac) and the people of France," he
said. 
</P>
